3
00:00:13,323 --> 00:00:15,165
to present Lessons from Duolingo,

4
00:00:15,805 --> 00:00:18,166
How to Turn Good Intentions into Good Numbers.

5
00:00:19,047 --> 00:00:22,429
This talk will go over how to leverage a data-driven culture

6
00:00:22,589 --> 00:00:24,851
to further your business metrics while still

7
00:00:24,891 --> 00:00:26,312
staying true to your values.

8
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:29,174
I'll start by doing a quick introduction.

9
00:00:29,514 --> 00:00:30,615
My name is Karen Tsai.

10
00:00:31,344 --> 00:00:34,766
I have a BSc in computer science and a minor in neuroscience

11
00:00:34,786 --> 00:00:36,066
from Princeton University.

12
00:00:36,567 --> 00:00:38,908
So I've always been interested in the intersection

13
00:00:38,948 --> 00:00:40,449
of education and technology.

14
00:00:41,409 --> 00:00:43,290
Currently, I'm an engineering director

15
00:00:43,590 --> 00:00:45,511
at Duolingo, the most popular way

16
